          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> curry powder </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 80ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [120ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and cook for 2 min further or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>curried béchamel</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
